<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lawless" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lawless,</orth> 1) contrary to law, illegal: <cit><quote>no indirect nor l. course,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.224" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 224</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) unruly, licentious: <cit><quote>our l. lives,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. and incertain thought,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 127</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this l. bloody book of rebellion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy l. sons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.312" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 312</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>l. resolutes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 98</bibl></cit> (Ff <emph>landless</emph>). <cit><quote>in his l. fit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 8</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>